      "body" : "qtipcserver: Yea, I thought about doing that but I didnt feel like shuffling even more code around instead of just porting what I already had...Ill move the files to qt/ at least.\r\nThreadSafeHandleURL: I would prefer it did, seems like it would be less of a DDoS target if it limited the number of queued objects to at least what boost will allow (2 in this case) and then limit to what Qt will be able to handle\r\nJS DDos: probably a good idea to test and see how high one can get Bitcoin's CPU usage to go (also limit the number of queued payment boxes in Bitcoin's ui?).\r\nIn terms of adding yet another dialog box, I dont think its necessary, Bitcoin will already confirm before sending.",
